---
layout: layouts/listing.njk
title: Suttas
description: Selected suttas from the Pali canon — structure, content, and what they ask of the reader.
---

<header class="page-header">
  <p class="page-header__eyebrow">Suttas</p>
  <h1 class="page-header__title">Discourses</h1>
  <p class="page-header__subtitle">
    Specific texts from the Pali canon — what they contain, how they work,
    what they ask of the reader.
  </p>
</header>

<p class="section-intro">
  A sutta is not a theorem to be proved or a story to be enjoyed — it is, in most cases,
  a record of a teaching delivered to a particular person in a particular situation.
  Reading them well means holding that context in mind.
  For stock phrases, repetition, and a workable two-pass method, see
  <a href="/concepts/how-to-read-a-sutta/">How to Read a Sutta</a>.
</p>

<ul class="entry-list">

  {% for item in collections.suttas %}
  <li class="entry-list__item">
    <a class="entry-list__link" href="{{ item.url }}">
      {% if item.data.thumb %}
      <span class="entry-list__thumb" aria-hidden="true">
        <img
          src="/images/thumbs/{{ item.data.thumb }}"
          alt=""
          width="400"
          height="300"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        >
      </span>
      {% endif %}
      <span class="entry-list__body">
        <span class="entry-list__meta">{{ item.data.meta }}</span>
        <span class="entry-list__title">{{ item.data.title }}</span>
        <span class="entry-list__excerpt">{{ item.data.excerpt }}</span>
      </span>
    </a>
  </li>
  {% endfor %}

</ul>
